abstract: They are focusing on areas where Hillary Clinton prevailed, but also on districts where they hope to win back voters they lost to Mr. Trump last year.

lead_paragraph: ANAHEIM, Calif. — Eileen Aispur tried to contain a bless-your-heart-level giggle as she listened to David Min, a Democrat, explain why she should consider him for a House seat representing this hill-ringed, steamy district south of Los Angeles. “We’re all Republicans here,” she blurted.

abstract: A veteran political reporter takes stock of how Washington has — and hasn’t — changed in the time of Trump.
snippet: A veteran political reporter takes stock of how Washington has — and hasn’t — changed in the time of Trump.
lead_paragraph: Sean Spicer, the White House press secretary, was running late and ‘‘tied up in the Oval,’’ an assistant explained. It was late on a Thursday afternoon in June, and I had not seen Spicer since the election that would supposedly transform the accustomed reality of Washington and had unquestionably upended his.

snippet: “Homecoming,” the sixth web-crawler story to arrive on the big screen in 15 years, took in about $117 million in the United States and Canada over the weekend.
lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — Spider-Man swung back into theaters in triumphant fashion over the weekend, prompting a window-rattling sigh of relief from Sony Pictures, which has been struggling to end a prolonged fallow period at the box office.

headline_main: ‘Spider-Man’ Still Has Box Office Bite, to Sony’s Relief
headline_print_headline: With a Box Office Bite, Spider-Man Is No. 1

abstract: After a humiliating 2014 cyberattack that helped lead to her ouster at Sony Pictures, the producer decided her life in the movie business was far from over.
snippet: After a humiliating 2014 cyberattack that helped lead to her ouster at Sony Pictures, the producer decided her life in the movie business was far from over.
lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — After 18 years at Sony Pictures, the last 11 as studio boss, a position that made her one of the most powerful people in Hollywood, Amy Pascal had her life blown apart.

lead_paragraph: Welcome, friend. Surely you’ve glanced at the photo of the Volvo V90 Cross Country and understood that it’s a station wagon. And yet you read on. Possibly you’re an original thinker and open-minded about wagons.

abstract: An industry has sprouted to help Muslims who choose halal investing, which is guided by Islamic rules and principles.
snippet: An industry has sprouted to help Muslims who choose halal investing, which is guided by Islamic rules and principles.
lead_paragraph: When faced with a loss in the market versus a lapse in his faith, Nabeel Hamoui, 37, a radiologist in Chicago, will invariably opt for the loss. This is because Dr. Hamoui manages his retirement portfolio in accordance with halal, or religiously sanctioned, Islamic guidelines.

abstract: Luther is the daughter of the three-time Olympic medalist Whitney Hedgepeth, with a six-time Olympic medalist, Brendan Hansen, as a coach.
snippet: Luther is the daughter of the three-time Olympic medalist Whitney Hedgepeth, with a six-time Olympic medalist, Brendan Hansen, as a coach.
lead_paragraph: INDIANAPOLIS — Dakota Luther’s coach, Brendan Hansen, won six medals in three Olympics. Her mother, Whitney Hedgepeth, won three medals in two Olympics. But down the stretch of the women’s 200-meter butterfly final at the USA Swimming national championships, none of that mattered.
